SOURCE

CORDIS http://cordis.europa.eu/news/rcn/128663_en.html

AGENT

Prof Alessandro Bogliolo from the University of Urbino.

GOAL

Detect road surface anomalies.

DATA

Smart phone app gathers accelerometer and gyroscope data.

METHODS

Supervised Machine Learning.

RESULTS

An open data set with more than 2 000 000 records, automatically updated every 6 hours with crowd-sensed data, has been published.

COMMENTS

Could optimise how we choose roads to repair improving the efficiency of the Council services.